# Repository context

The canonical, complete guide for working in this repo is **`AGENTS.md`** at the
repo root — read it before writing or editing code. Key facts:

- Static, **no-framework** mockup tool for manager review of a redesigned HHVC
  section of SF.gov. `index.html` loads plain classic `<script>` tags directly.
  **Plain browser JavaScript, not TypeScript** — no bundler, no ES
  modules/`import`/`export` in `js/*.js`. **Bun** runs the dev server, CLI
  scripts, and tests.
- **Prettier is the only linter** (`.prettierrc.json`): no semicolons, single
  quotes, 2-space indent, 100-char width, ES5 trailing commas. Code must be
  ASI-safe. Run `bun run format` before committing. `bun run format:check` is the
  lint step.
- **Data-driven rendering:** `pages/*.js` assign onto `window.HHVC_PAGES`;
  `js/page-data.js` builds `window.HHVC_DATA`. **Script load order in
  `index.html` matters** (classic `<script>` tags share one global scope).
- **`karl` fields are first-class content**, not comments. Never hand-edit
  generated files (single-file HTML exports, `data/page_inventory.*`).
- **Tests exist:** `bun run test` (7 Bun unit files) + `bun run test:e2e`
  (Playwright); `bun run validate` Zod-validates all pages. Run validate + test
  after editing `pages/*.js` or `js/page-data.js`.
- **Commits:** imperative mood, Conventional-Commits prefixes for code; keep
  dashboard-UX and policy-copy changes in separate PRs.
- Write **detailed, explanatory** comments that justify the _why_.

See `AGENTS.md` for the full architecture, page-object schema, validation
invariants, JS/CSS idioms, and commit/PR conventions. The `design.mdc` rule in
this directory is a separate, design-only workflow that applies **only** when you
are asked to do UI/visual design.
